ing for many months which route to take ceo peter huntsman said now that the struggling pigments and additives business is becoming profitable again  back in the black  his company can gain more value by spinning off the unit and selling shares than by selling it outright the new company would focus specifically on titanium dioxide chemical called tio which is used as a pigment for everything from food coloring and paints to coatings and sunscreen a spin allows us to have a process that we can control huntsman said noting that shareholders should benefit this is something that has greater certainty behind it huntsman has sought to unload or at least distance itself from the titanium dioxide business because its poor performance has weighed on huntsmans stock price translator to read this article in one of houstons mostspoken languages click on the button below business calpine confirms its negotiating sale bbva compass quarterly earnings bode well for near future lingering pain as houston energy services firms slice more jobs former politician looks to permian britain to ban new diesel and gas cars by  has fracking reached peak sand hassan ahmed a chemical industry analyst of new yorkbased alembic global advisors said spinning off the unit could prove wise because the titanium dioxide business is cyclical and makes investors wary of huntsman in addition the new company might be attractive to investors now because the pigments industry is out of the cyclical trough he said giving a timeline  rather than some pieinthesky thing  is better than expected ahmed said of the spinoff last year was termed a transition year for huntsman after the  purchase of  billion in plants and other assets from rockwood holdings a chemical company owned by albemarle corp of charlotte nc huntsmans biggest financial drag has been its titanium dioxide plants some of which were purchased from rockwood huntsman is in the process of closing its smallest titanium dioxide plant which is in south africa the company began eliminating at least  jobs last year most of them at three titanium dioxide manufacturing plants in germany and finland huntsman which employs more than  people in the houston area has dual headquarters in texas and utah which is the seat of the huntsman family dynasty in utah peter huntsmans brother jon is a former utah governor and gop presidential candidate huntsman corp reported that its profit for the second quarter tripled from the same period a year earlier due in part to cost cutting profit rose to  million from  million in  even though the specialty chemical companys revenue fell to  billion from  billion last year despite the profit huntsmans net earnings are below its historic norms huntsmans stock fell wednesday to  per share down  cents houston trump spotlights brutal ms gang houston politics  policy public works director steps down over bribery case business oil industry continues to recover but focused on texas brian t smith generations of astros fans follow bagwell to cooperstown top about our company ad choices careers terms of use advertising privacy policy your privacy rights your california privacy rights contact subscribe enewspaper archives customer service frequently asked questions newsroom contacts connect newsletters facebook twitter linkedin pinterest google connect   hearst newspapers llc products english  locations contacti servicei privacyi cookiesi codes of conducti sitemap print email   searching  search site  search technical datasheet products products   a b c d e f g h i j k l m n o p q r s t u v w x y z accelerators a substance that increases the rate of a chemical reaction eg the curing of the epoxy resins acoustiflex® a range of mdi based polyurethanes technologies designed to provide superior acoustic absorption advanced comfort™ with huntsman’s patented advanced comfort™ foam technology comfort and durability come together in an exceptional combination advanced materials formerly vantico advanced mater