t venator will be a premier pigments company unencumbered by excessive debt or other unrelated liabilities improved titanium dioxide pricing combined with the identification of business improvement opportunities that are incremental to current earnings are expected to more than offset the free cash flow that venator would have received from the textile effects business” huntsman has been planning to separate its pigments and additives division through either a spinoff to shareholders or other strategic transaction for some time now the company restructured the division — including announcing  job cuts in december  and closing its titanium dioxide manufacturing facility in south africa last year— in preparation for the split an initial public offering was planned for the division shortly after huntsman announced it would pay  billion in cash to acquire the pigment business of princeton new yorkbased rockwood holdings inc nyse roc in september  olivia pulsinelli is the senior web editor for the houston business journals awardwinning website follow her on twitter for more related content ceo huntsman to continue expanding in the woodlands bizspace spotlight sponsor listing property spotlight class a office space  clear lake see all bizspace properties industries manufacturing suggested reading read the digital weekly edition view current issue houston tx industry news  houston business journal menu select a city national albany albuquerque atlanta austin baltimore birmingham boston buffalo charlotte chicago cincinnati columbus dallas dayton denver greensborowinstonsalem honolulu houston jacksonville kansas city los angeles louisville memphis miamifort lauderdale milwaukee minneapolisst paul nashville new york orlando philadelphia phoenix pittsburgh portland raleighdurham sacramento san antonio san francisco seattle silicon valley st louis tampa bay washington dc wichita limited time offer subscribe now search × close sign in sign in your account your account welcome yo